{"sha": "b5de94fba9a137a1128448f4b703250e7e8ff975", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOmI1ZGU5NGZiYTlhMTM3YTExMjg0NDhmNGI3MDMyNTBlN2U4ZmY5NzU=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "bors", "email": "bors@rust-lang.org", "date": "2016-04-17T06:06:29Z"}, "committer": {"name": "bors", "email": "bors@rust-lang.org", "date": "2016-04-17T06:06:29Z"}, "message": "Auto merge of #32977 - alexcrichton:ignore-panics, r=brson\n\nstd: Change String::truncate to panic less\n\nThe `Vec::truncate` method does not panic if the length argument is greater than\nthe vector's current length, but `String::truncate` will indeed panic. This\nsemantic difference can be a bit jarring (e.g. #32717), and after some\ndiscussion the libs team concluded that although this can technically be a\nbreaking change it is almost undoubtedly not so in practice.\n\nThis commit changes the semantics of `String::truncate` to be a noop if\n`new_len` is greater than the length of the current string.\n\nCloses #32717", "tree": {"sha": "57b28ae22fc683cd89d65477466375e335c09218", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/57b28ae22fc683cd89d65477466375e335c09218"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/b5de94fba9a137a1128448f4b703250e7e8ff975", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/b5de94fba9a137a1128448f4b703250e7e8ff975", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/b5de94fba9a137a1128448f4b703250e7e8ff975", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/b5de94fba9a137a1128448f4b703250e7e8ff975/comments", "author": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/followe